  <td width="78"><strong>POSITION:</strong></td><td width="482">Associate, PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center</td></tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>SUPERVISOR:</strong></td><td>Julie Hertzog, Director, PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center</td></tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>STATUS:</strong></td><td>Full Time, Exempt</td></tr>
</table>

<h2 style="margin-top:30px;">RESPONSIBILITIES:</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Respond to email and phone requests, inquiries and contacts for PACER&rsquo;s National Bullying Prevention Center. Enter all contents in contact database.</li>
  <li>Assist with writing and designing content for students, educators and parents on bullying prevention.</li>
  <li>Serve as an advocate on the topic of bullying prevention for students, parents and educators.</li>
  <li>Assist in public information and education activities with presentations to various organizations and professional groups. </li>
  <li>Respond to requests and information for celebrity partnering, products for promotion and fundraisers.</li>
  <li>Review and provide assessment of requests for submission of stories, video and image.</li>
  <li>Keep current on best practices for bullying prevention strategies. </li>
  <li>Manage events; such as Run, Walk, Roll Against Bullying and Unity Day.</li>
  <li>Assist with new promotions, initiatives, and campaigns created in partnership with corporations, foundations, and individuals.</li>
  <li>Coordinate youth leadership group.</li>
  <li>Write and post social media updates.</li>
  <li>Audit online databases, including petition entry and updating &ldquo;I Care Because . . . &ldquo;</li>
  <li>Maintain records of activities.</li>
  <li>Write grants proposals.</li>
  <li>Solicit individuals for donations.</li>
  <li>Additional duties and responsibilities as needed.</li>
</ol>
<h2 style="margin-top:30px;">REQUIREMENTS:</h2>
<ul>
  <li>College degree or equivalent background gained through training or work experience</li>
  <li>Excellent communications skills and ability to relate to diverse groups.</li>
  <li>Experience and skill in public speaking, writing, and training. </li>
  <li>Ability to work collaboratively with internal staff and community partners.</li>
  <li>Ability to provide own transportation and flexibility to travel</li>
  <li>Excellent organizational skills, ability to meet deadlines</li>
  <li>Ability to keep good records and collect data for evaluation purposes</li>
  <li>Experience in community service/human service/social service.</li>
</ul>
<p>Parents of children  with disabilities are encouraged to apply.<br />
  Salary to be determined based on experience. Position available immediately.</p>
<p>Send resume with a  letter of application to:<br />
  Mary Jackson |  PACER Center | 8161 Normandale Blvd | Minneapolis, MN 55437</p>
<p>PACER Center is an <em>Affirmative</em> <em>Action and Equal  Employment Opportunity</em> Employer.<br />
